<HEADLINE> Chinese FM Speaks at U.N. General Assembly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign
Minister Tang Jiaxuan, head of the Chinese delegation to the 53rd
General Assembly session, Wednesday delivered a speech at the
session.
</P>
<P>
Tang took the floor to speak on the Chinese government's views
on a wide range of issues of international concern, including the
complete prohibition and thorough destruction of nuclear weapons,
the impact of the East Asian financial crisis, the Middle East
peace process and the situation in Kosovo, the Federal Republic of
Yugoslavia.
</P>
<P>
In his speech, Tang also touched upon the reform of the United
Nations and China's active role in promoting peace and development
in the world.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese foreign minister also briefed the current session
on China's flood-fighting and disaster-relief efforts.
</P>
<P>
"With full confidence, we are taking every measure possible to
ensure that there will be no famine and no widespread epidemic
diseases in the wake of the natural disaster and no dropouts or
anyone deprived of education among pupils and students in the
flood-hit areas," he added.
</P>
<P>
It is the first time for Tang to deliver his speech at the
General Assembly session since he became the Chinese foreign
minister early this year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
