<HEADLINE> Pakistan Says Striving to Remove Iran-Afghan Tension </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan is effectively
playing a reconciliatory role in efforts to remove tension between
Iran and Afghanistan, Chairman of the Standing Committee of the
National Assembly on Foreign Affairs Abdul Waheed said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a press conference here, Waheed said the meeting
between Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif and Iranian President Mohammad
Khatami in New York helped to remove misgivings between the two
countries.
</P>
<P>
He said Sharif should also pay a visit to Iran, which would
help reduce the tension.
</P>
<P>
Waheed said if the tension between Iran and Afghanistan
escalated it would have disastrous consequences in the region and
in central Asian states as well.
</P>
<P>
He said there were certain elements which were fanning the
situation.
</P>
<P>
Waheed regretted the killing of Iranian diplomats in
Afghanistan. He also said it was satisfying to note that the
Iranian leadership was in realization of the fact that war was not
advantageous to any one.  
