<DOCNO> XIE19980924.0016 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tang on Human Rights in World, China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The right to
development has been universally recognized in the international
community as an inseparable part of the basic human rights,
Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
This year marks the 50th anniversary of the adoption of the
Universal Declaration of Human Rights, said Tang, head of the
Chinese delegation to the 53rd General Assembly session. He added
that the declaration has vigorously promoted the advancement and
development of the cause of human rights in the world.
</P>
<P>
The vast numbers of people in Asia, Africa and Latin America
freed themselves from colonial rule, he said, adding that the
South African people rooted out the dark system of apartheid, won
basic political rights and became an equal member in the
international community.
</P>
<P>
"The United Nations for its part passed a series of
international instruments on human rights such as the Declaration
of the Right to Development, further enriching the content of
human right," he said. "The right to development has been
universally recognized in the international community as an
inseparable part of the basic human rights."
</P>
<P>
In the meantime, earth-shaking changes have taken place in
China, he said, adding that especially in the past two decades
since the introduction of reform and opening-up, China has
witnessed ever-improved practice of democracy and legal system and
ever-enhanced legal protection of the rights of the people.
</P>
<P>
"It is perfectly obvious that the Chinese people now enjoy a
higher degree of freedom and equality than ever before and a much
more colorful and settled life than in the past," Tang said. "The
Chinese government will continue to make unremitting efforts to
advance democracy and strengthen the legal system while developing
the economy so as to better ensure that its people enjoy human
rights to the full."
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government is active in supporting and
participating in the activities of the United Nations in the field
of human rights, he said.
</P>
<P>
"China has all along stood for international cooperation in the
field of human rights on the basis of equality and mutual respect
so as to enhance understanding, narrow differences, expand common
ground and strengthen cooperation through dialogue," he said.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese government is ready to engage in dialogue,
exchange and cooperation on the basis of equality and mutual
respect with human rights organizations at national and
international levels," he said.
</P>
<P>
Last October, the Chinese government signed the International
Covenant on Economic, Social and Cultural Rights, he said. "As to
the International Covenant on Civil and Political Rights, I
earnestly declare here that the Chinese government has decided to
sign it early next month."
</P>
<P>
"This once again testifies to the resolve of the Chinese
government on promoting and protecting human rights," he said.
</P>
<P>
"China is ready to continue to work with other countries to
maintain and push the current positive momentum of dialogue and
cooperation so as to promote the furtherance of the world cause of
human rights," he said. 
</P>
