<HEADLINE> African Experts on Population and Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 23 (Xinhua) -- African population
experts started here Wednesday a three-day meeting to evaluate
implementation of Dakar/Ngor Declaration on Africa's population
and development.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the opening ceremony here, K.Y. Amoako, Executive
Secretary of the United Nations Economic Commission for Africa
(ECA), said the current Third Meeting of the Follow-Up Committee
is expected to review and appraise implementation of the meetings
at Ngor and Cairo.
</P>
<P>
He urged the participants at the meeting to strive to identify
specific activities that can accelerate the implementation of
Ngor and Cairo meetings, for a sustainable development on the
continent.
</P>
<P>
The official also asked the third meeting to systematically
examine the various constraints that have been identified in
earlier assessments, and propose recommendations that can
effectively address them.
</P>
<P>
African country experts in population policies and programs,
representatives from the Organization of African Unity (OAU),
African Development Bank (ADB) and sub-regional institutions as
well as from international non-Governmental organizations are
attending the three-day meeting jointly sponsored by the ECA, OAU
and ADB.
</P>
<P>
According to a press release issued by the ECA, the Third
Meeting will discuss successes and challenges in population
control and development.  
</P>
