<HEADLINE> Cyprus to Host Euro-Mediterranean Services </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NICOSIA, September 23 (Xinhua) -- The 4th Euro-Mediterranean
Services Exhibition will open in Cyprus on October 8 to promote
the island's service industry.
</P>
<P>
A total of 32 companies and organizations from Cyprus, Greece,
Egypt, Jordan, Lebanon and Malta will participate in the
exhibition called "CyServ '98."
</P>
<P>
At a press conference on the show Wednesday, Director General
of the Cyprus' Employers and Industrialists Federation Antonis
Pierides said that the exhibition is a major event, which
constitutes a "bridge for Euro-Mediterranean cooperation" in
services sector.
</P>
<P>
He said participants will include companies and organizations
related to the services sector such as consultancy, accounting,
advertising, information-technology, market research, banking,
tourism and education.
</P>
<P>
Pierides also noted that Cyprus' economic future lies in the
services sector, whose revenues at present accounts for around 73
percent of the country's gross domestic product.
</P>
<P>
A public debate on promoting Cypriot services export and an
international conference, named Business Centers of the Future,
will be held on the sidelines of the exhibition. 
