<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Over 500,000 Greek Landowners Register Properties </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 23 (Xinhua) -- More than 500,000 landowners
in Greece had registered their properties under the national land
register program, Greece's Environment, Town Planning and Public
Works Minister Costas Laliotis said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
He said that the registration rate for areas which are being
catalogued was close to 90 percent.
</P>
<P>
Greece and neighboring Albania are the only European countries
without a land register which aims to protect public lands from
encroachment as well as provide revenues for the state and create
jobs.
</P>
<P>
To receive a title of ownership to land, applicants should pay
duty of between 10,000 drachmas (about 33 U.S. dollars) and
300,000 drachmas (about 1,000 dollars) in accordance with the
value of the property.
</P>
<P>
The next phase of the project would reportedly involve
properties in 447 local government authorities or 16 percent of
Greece's total urban area, 10 percent of total farm land and 7
percent of other forms of land. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
