<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Keeps Positive Attitude to WTO Entry, Tang Says </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 23 (Xinhua) -- China continues to
take a positive attitude towards its accession to the World Trade
Organization (WTO) and such an entry "will benefit all its members
and make the multilateral trade mechanism complete and more
balanced," Chinese Foreign Minister Tang Jiaxuan said here
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing the 53rd General Assembly session, Tang said, "China
continues to take a positive attitude towards its accession to the
WTO. Thanks to the unremitting efforts of China over a decade,
China is already qualified for entry."
</P>
<P>
"Regrettably, however, the relevant negotiations have dragged
on and on with no decision made," he said.
</P>
<P>
"China is a developing country, and we can only negotiate
China's entry into the WTO on this basis in accordance with the
principle of balancing the rights and obligations," he said.
</P>
<P>
"It is our hope that the countries concerned will take a
practical, fair and flexible attitude, give up excessive demands
and work for an early conclusion of the relevant negotiations," he
said.
</P>
<P>
"China's accession to the WTO will benefit all its members and
make the multilateral trade mechanism complete and more balanced,"
he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
