<HEADLINE> French President Supports Russia in Fighting Crisis </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, September 23 (Xinhua) -- French President Jacques
Chirac Wednesday said that he fully and resolutely supports
Russia's anti-crisis efforts, according to the Interfax news
agency.
</P>
<P>
This remark was voiced by Chirac in a telephone conversation
with Russian President Boris Yeltsin Wednesday evening.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin, on his part, told the French president the formation
of the Cabinet and the steps taken by him and the government to
stabilize the situation.
</P>
<P>
The Russian presidential press service said that the
conversation took place in the spirit of continuing the regular
Russian-French top-level dialogue.
</P>
<P>
The formation of the new Russian government has not been
concluded. The Russian president by far has appointed the prime
minister, five deputy prime ministers, including two first deputy
prime ministers, and some key government ministers.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the work on the government's anti-crisis program is
under way. 
</P>
