<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Istanbul Mayor Sentenced to 10-Month Imprisonment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Turkey's Supreme Court of
Appeals Wednesday upheld sentence of a ten-month imprisonment for
pro-Islamic Istanbul Mayor Tayyip Erdogan.
</P>
<P>
Erdogan was found guilty by the State Security Court in
Diyarbair, southeast Turkey, in April "for inciting hatred based
on religious differences" in a speech at a political rally.
</P>
<P>
This court decision will go to the Interior Ministry, which
will ask the Council of State to end Erdogan's tenure as mayor, TV
reports said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Chief Prosecutor Vural Savas has already asked the appeals
court to act with speed to uphold the verdict and accused Erdogan
of being a "cheap bully."
</P>
<P>
"Minarets are our bayonets, domes are our helmets, Mosques are
our barracks, believers are our soldiers," Erdogan said in the
April rally, reading from a folk poem by nationalist poet Ziya
Gokalp. 
</P>
</TEXT>
