<HEADLINE> Canadians Massively Buy Foreign Stocks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Canadians bought a massive 12
billion Canadian dollars(7.8 billion U.S. dollars) in foreign
stocks in the nine-month period of November to July, Statistics
Canada reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
In July alone Canadians purchased 2.5 billion Canadian dollars
(1.6 billion U.S. dollars) in foreign securities while foreign
investment in Canadian securities remained a low 900 million
Canadian dollars (585 million U.S. dollars), said the government
agency.
</P>
<P>
Canadian foreign-security purchases involved 1.5 billion
Canadian dollars (975 million U.S. dollars) and 1 billion Canadian
dollars (650 million U.S. dollars) in bonds.
</P>
<P>
Foreigners reduced holdings of Canadian money market paper by
1.9 billion Canadian dollars (1.2 billion U.S. dollars) in July,
bringing their disinvestment for May, June and July to 6.9 billion
Canadian dollars (4.5 billion U.S. dollars). They bought 2.7
billion Canadian dollars (1.8 billion U.S. dollars) worth of
Canadian bonds in july. 
</P>
