<HEADLINE> 100,000 People Ordered to Evacuate Before </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Up to 100,000 people were
ordered to begin evacuating the exposed Florida Keys island chain
Wednesday before Hurricane Georges lands, reports reaching here
said.
</P>
<P>
South Florida was put under a hurricane watch as the storm
moved across open water between Haiti and eastern Cuba, telling
local residents hurricane-force wind of at least 118 kph could
reach the area by late Thursday.
</P>
<P>
Georges was barely a hurricane Wednesday with sustained wind
around the center of only 120 kph, making it a Category one storm.
Strengthening was possible and could trigger precautionary
mainland evacuations as early as Wednesday night.
</P>
<P>
Governor Lawton Chiles declared a state of emergency in central
and southern Florida, allowing the state to use the National
Guard, lift tolls along evacuation routes and purchase emergency
supplies.
</P>
<P>
Elderly residents dependent on electric medical equipment
already had been flown to Sebring in central Florida. And 200
nursing home patients were sent to a Key West immigration center
that would serve as a shelter during the storm. 
</P>
</TEXT>
