<HEADLINE> ASEAN Foreign Ministers Meet in New York </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The Singapore government
said in a statement Thursday that the ASEAN foreign ministers met
in New York on September 23 and discussed the Cambodia issue and
the participations for the ASEAN summit scheduled for December in
Hanoi, Vietnam.
</P>
<P>
The statement, issued by Foreign Minister J. Jayakumar in the
capacity of the ASEAN Standing Committee, said that the meeting
reviewed the developments in Cambodia following the elections and
expressed the hope that political stability in Cambodia will be
restored quickly.
</P>
<P>
It also said the foreign ministers discussed the question of
Cambodia's admission into ASEAN and agreed that ASEAN take a
decision on the timing of Cambodia's admission into ASEAN only
after a new government is formed in Cambodia.
</P>
<P>
Without a government in place, the statement said, Cambodia
will not be able to assume the full rights and obligations of
ASEAN membership.
</P>
<P>
According to the statement, the meeting was briefed by
Vietnamese Foreign Minister Nguyen Manh Cam on the preparations
for the ASEAN summit and ASEAN endorsed the candidature of Thai
Deputy Prime Minister Supachai Panitchpakdi for the post of WTO
director-general and Indonesia's candidature to the Economic and
Social Council at the 53rd United Nations General Assembly.
</P>
<P>
ASEAN groups Brunei, Indonesia, Laos, Malaysia, Myanmar, the
Philippines, Singapore, Thailand and Vietnam. 
</P>
</TEXT>
