<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Matthew Dunn sets short-course record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Commonwealth Games gold
medalist Matthew Dunn set his second world record in two weeks at
the Australian short course swimming championships in Perth on
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The 25-year-old shaved more than a second off the listed time
for the 400-meter individual medley by winning in a time of four
minutes, 4.24 seconds in the 25-meter pool.
</P>
<P>
The previous record of 4:05.41 was held by Martel Wouda of the
Netherlands.
</P>
<P>
Dunn was also a member of the world record-breaking 4x200
freestyle relay team in Kuala Lumpur last week.
</P>
<P>
Earlier in the night, 15-year-old Ian Thorpe broke a
Commonwealth record in the men's 200-meter freestyle.
</P>
<P>
Thorpe beat Michael Klim in 1:44.37 to lower the record by
0.84 of a second. Klim finished strongly and also broke his own
record with a time of 1:44.61. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
