<HEADLINE> British Helicopter Crashes During Exercise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 24 (Xinhua) -- A British Lynx helicopter
taking part in a joint Singapore-British naval training exercise
crashed into the South China Sea Wednesday night, Singapore's
Minister of Defense confirmed Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said in a press release that of the two British
personnel aboard the helicopter, the pilot had been recovered and
found suffering minor bruises while the other was still missing.
</P>
<P>
According to the ministry, the incident occurred when the Lynx
helicopter of Britain's Royal Navy was flying together with a
Fokker-50 maritime Patrol Aircraft of Singapore's Air Force on a
mission to provide support for a night encounter exercise between
Singapore's three missile corvettes and a British ship.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said a search and rescue operation had been
launched to locate the missing personnel. 
</P>
