<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Issues Management Rules on Genetic Resources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- China's Ministry of Science
and Technology and the Ministry of Health have jointly issued the
Provisional Regulations on the Management of Genetic Resources.
</P>
<P>
The regulations were formulated on the basis of proposals
tabled by departments and experts concerned, according to official
sources.
</P>
<P>
The goal of the regulations is to effectively protect and
ensure the rational use of the nation's genetic resources for the
well-being of human beings, promote related international
cooperation and exchanges on the basis of equality and mutual
benefit, and safeguard the legal rights of those involved in
related research programs.
</P>
<P>
All the activities involved in the collection, research,
development, marketing and both imports and exports of genetic
resources will be subject to the regulations.
</P>
<P>
International programs and all imports and exports will be
subject to official approval from authorized departments.
</P>
<P>
Those engaged in securing genetic materials must inform both
the donor and his/her relatives in advance.
</P>
<P>
The ministries plan to establish a joint management office, and
an expert team will be formed to conduct routine operations. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
