<HEADLINE> Shenzhen Leads China in TV Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Shenzhen, one of China's
special economic zones, produced 4.37 million TV sets during the
first seven months of this year.
</P>
<P>
The city has replaced Mianyang, southwest China's Sichuan Province, as
China's major television production base. Mianyang is home to
Changhong Group, the nation's leading television manufacturer.
</P>
<P>
Konka television sets manufactured in Shenzhen held 18.4 percent
of the retail market in July, and continued to hold the lead in sales
throughout August. 
