<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnam: Foreign Interference Poses Great Threat to Security </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The Vietnamese defense ministry
said Thursday that foreign interference in the country's internal
affairs constitutes a great threat to its national security.
</P>
<P>
To defend security, sovereignty and territorial integrity, the
ministry said, Vietnam has the right to build military strength
and an army with better weapons, equipment and technologies.
</P>
<P>
While making public Vietnam's defense goals, policies and tasks
in its first white paper released Thursday, the ministry did not
provide details as to the size and budget of the military.
</P>
<P>
"The plots to interfere in Vietnam's internal affairs in the
disguise of 'human rights' or 'democracy,' the intrusion into this
country by means of culture and ideology, activities of subversion
and destabilization for the purpose of replacing the current
political and social system, are all great menaces to Vietnam's
security and national defense," it said.
</P>
<P>
As the political situation is stabilized and national defense
maintained after over 10 years of renovation, it said, maintaining
sovereignty, national security and territorial integrity would
still be the "first and most important task."
</P>
<P>
The ministry repeated the Vietnamese government's position that
it would not align with one country against another, nor seek
confrontation and take offensive actions against any other country.
</P>
<P>
The country now needs to create an international environment
favorable to its cause of national construction, economic
development and raising the people's living standards, it said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
