<HEADLINE> Private Donations for Flood Relief </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- China's private
businesses have donated some 850 million yuan to support
relief efforts in areas devastated by severe summer flooding,
according to official statistics.
</P>
<P>
Seven private companies have donated more than 10 million yuan
each, with an additional 130 private firms contributing over one
million yuan each.
</P>
<P>
The donations fully demonstrate the patriotic enthusiasm of
local private businesses, as well as their sense of social
responsibility.
</P>
<P>
This year's summer flooding killed 3,004 people and affected an
240 million people by varying degrees. Large-scale charity
events to raise donations and materials have been carried
out across the nation over the past two months. 
</P>
