<HEADLINE> Zhu Rongji Meets French Prime Minister (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Zhu briefed Jospin and the French delegation on the current
economic situation in China.
</P>
<P>
He said China has faced two major challenges since the current
government was seated in March this year -- the financial crisis
engulfing Asia, and the severe summer flooding. But China's
reforms and opening-up process was not affected, nor was
realization of this year's economic goal.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders exchanged views on the worldwide financial
situation and voiced agreement over the need for global
cooperation.
</P>
<P>
Jospin praised China's refusal to devalue the Renminbi and
devotion to maintaining the stability of international currencies.
</P>
<P>
He praised Chinese soldiers and citizens for their dauntless
heroism in battling summer flooding.
</P>
<P>
Jospin also expressed appreciation for China's continuing to
carry out reform and opening. He noted his deep impression of
great changes which have taken place in China.
</P>
<P>
He said the French government values friendship and bilateral
ties, and highly values China's position and role in the
international community.
</P>
<P>
France is fully prepared to join China in building a
comprehensive partnership geared to the 21st century, said Jospin,
adding that continuing bilateral exchanges fully display the
French government's willingness to consolidate the significant
relations.
</P>
<P>
Zhu and Jospin attended a ceremony in which representatives
from the two governments signed a finance protocol, program of
action for developing advanced information technology, an agreement
on the protection of intellectual property rights, and a
cooperative agreement between China's Science and Technology
Ministry and the Electricity de France.
</P>
<P>
The French prime minister is visiting China at the invitation
of Premier Zhu Rongji. 
</P>
