<HEADLINE> X Newcastle Manager Dalglish Blasts' Attack Claims </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Former Newcastle manager
Kenny Dalglish hit out Thursday at claims that he was attacked by
fans after traveling to Rotherham to watch his son play for the
Magpies' reserves
</P>
<P>
Dalglish senior was at Millmoor on Tuesday night to see son
Paul score his side's second goal in a 4-0 Pontin's League win.
</P>
<P>
But he vehemently denied press reports that first he and then
his car were attacked by United supporters as he left the ground
after the game.
