<HEADLINE> HK Retail Sales for July Decrease </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The value of total retail
sales in Hong Kong in July was estimated at 17.0 billion HK
dollars (2.18 billion U.S. dollars), down by 17 percent over
a year earlier, official figures showed.
</P>
<P>
According to the provisional figures on retail sales released
Thursday by the Census and Statistics Department, total retail
sales after discounting the effect of price changes over the
period decreased also by 17 percent in volume.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the previous month, total retail sales in July
increased by 4 percent in volume, with an increase of 2 percent in
value.
</P>
<P>
Comparing the period from January to July 1998 with the same
period in 1997, total retail sales decreased by 15 percent in
value and 16 percent in volume. 
</P>
