<HEADLINE> Four-city Art Exchange Program Launched in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 24 (Xinhua) -- A rare dialogue among
partists from Guangzhou, Shenzhen, Hong Kong and Macao was launched
with the opening of an arts exhibition at the Hong Kong University
of Science and Technology here on Thursday.
</P>
<P>
"The Lingnan School of Chinese painting has exerted a great
influence on the development of arts in these four cities. Yet,
while sharing the same artistic heritage, artists from these
neighboring cities have seldom sought dialogue with each other,"
said Wong Shu Kit, one of the curators of the exchange program.
</P>
<P>
"We believe that a free exchange of ideas will inspire exciting
new development in the Lingnan region," he added. Lingnan is a
geographical term denoting the South China area.
</P>
<P>
The centerpiece of the month-long exchange program is an
exhibition of paintings and installation art by 12 artists from
the cities, with diverse background including traditional Chinese
painting, sculpture and contemporary installation arts. The theme
of the exhibition is "Four Sides."
</P>
<P>
In addition, a series of art talks, seminars and open forums
will be organized each Saturday through October to coincide with
the exhibition. 
</P>
</TEXT>
