<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vessels into HK Down, Capacity Up in 2nd Quarter </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 24 (Xinhua) -- In the second quarter of
1998, 10,802 ocean vessels with a total capacity of 52.5 million
net registered tons entered Hong Kong, according to the statistics
released Thursday by the Census and Statistics Department.
</P>
<P>
In the same period, there were 10,974 outgoing ocean vessels
with a total capacity of 52.4 million net registered tons.
</P>
<P>
Net registered ton (NRT) is a unit measure in volume terms of
the space of a vessel available for carrying passengers or goods.
One NRT is equivalent to 100 cubic feet.
</P>
<P>
Compared with the second quarter of 1997, the number of
incoming and outgoing vessels decreased by 3 percent and 2 percent
respectively, while the capacity of both incoming and outgoing
vessels increased by 4 percent.
</P>
<P>
In the second quarter of 1998, the total tonnage of seaborne
inward cargo increased by 2 percent over a year earlier to 24.3
million tons, the statistics said.
</P>
<P>
Of this total, seaborne imports increased by 5 percent to 20.6
million tons, while seaborne inward transshipment decreased by 8
percent to 3.7 million tons.
</P>
<P>
During the same period, the total tonnage of seaborne outward
cargo decreased by 7 percent over a year earlier to 9.7 million
tons.
</P>
<P>
This comprised 5.8 million tons of seaborne exports (domestic
exports and re-exports), representing a 4 percent decrease, and
4.0 million tons of seaborne outward transshipment, which
decreased by 12 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
