<DOCNO> XIE19980924.0104 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Opposes Any Form of International Terrorism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- China opposes any form of
international terrorism, the use of terrorist acts for political
purposes and violent acts carried out by any state, organization
or individual in violation of international conventions.
</P>
<P>
China Foreign Ministry Spokesman Zhu Bangzao made the remarks
this afternoon in a statement outlining China's stance on
international terrorism.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said that China also steadfastly opposes interference in
the internal affairs of any country, infringements of national
sovereignty and invasions of any nation under the pretext of
opposing terrorism. Zhu labeled such activities as "violations of
international law."
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has consistently advocated the
enhancement of state-to-state cooperation and has at the same time
adopted effective counterterrorism measures, said Zhu, adding that
"all countries should fulfill their international obligations."
</P>
<P>
The international community should extend the greatest possible
efforts to trace the source and social factors contributing to
international terrorism in order to "gradually reduce and
eventually uproot the scourge of terrorism," said Zhu.
</P>
<P>
Counterterrorism cooperation should be based on the principles
of mutual respect for sovereignty, territorial integrity and
noninterference in the internal affairs of other nations.
</P>
<P>
Zhu said China has extended great effort to combat
international terrorism and has signed many related international
agreements. He added that China has joined Interpol and
participated in negotiations the UN Special Counterterrorism
Commission has conducted concerning terrorist bombings and nuclear
terrorism.
</P>
<P>
China has also formulated relevant domestic laws designed to
provide legal guarantees for preventing and combating terrorism,
said Zhu.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China is fully prepared to join other nations in
the battle to eventually eliminate terrorism. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
