<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Floodwaters Uncover Mammoth Fossils In Northeastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARBIN, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Some mammoth fossils from the
Neolithic Age were recently discovered in the suburbs of the city
of Qiqihar in northeast China's Heilongjiang Province in a deep
groove that was worn down by floodwaters of the Nenjiang River.
</P>
<P>
Li Liankui, a farmer who found the fossils, explained that last
month he happened to see a long white object sticking out of the
gully when he was looking after his cattles on nearby grassland.
</P>
<P>
The fossils are three meters long and were identified as a
fossilized mammoth trunk. Archaeologists from the Gannan Culture
and Relics Administration say they believe that the mammoth was 9
meters long and 6 meters tall and weighed 6 to 7 tons.
</P>
<P>
Farmers also found 10 other fossils of mammoths and a
rhinoceros that included rib, leg and shoulder blade bones.
</P>
<P>
Scholars say the fossils show that a large number of
animals lived in the western part of what is now Heilongjiang from
12,000 years ago.
</P>
<P>
The mammoth is a relative of the modern elephant that lived in
cold regions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980924.0115 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese Population (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
From 1952 to 1978, China's GDP grew 4.7-fold, but per capita
GDP rose only 180 percent, but in the past two decades the GDP
increased 4.4 times and per capita GDP 3.7 times.
</P>
<P>
Average per-capita grain yields also increased from 319 kg in
1978 to 398 kg in 1997, and improvements in the standard of living
have meant health condition changes, with the death rate down to
6.5 per thousand, and the average life expectancy up to 70.83,
three years more than in 1981.
</P>
<P>
Family planning has also helped education. In the early 1980s,
22.8 percent of the people were illiterate or semi-literate, but
by 1997 the figure was down to 12.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
From 1982 to 1997, the number of people with a higher education
rose from six per thousand to 25, and the number of people with
senior and junior middle school educations was also up by a big
margin.
</P>
<P>
In 1982 the number of ethnic minorities was 67.3 million, or
5.93 percent of the total population, while in 1995 it rose to
108.46 million, 8.98 percent of the total population.
</P>
<P>
Every year, China adds some 20 million people for a net growth
of some 11 million, and further efforts should be made to ease the
pressure on social and economic development caused by the huge
population. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
