<HEADLINE> Chinese Legislator Speaks About Law-Enforcement Inspection Results </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Buhe, vice-chairman of the
Standing Committee of the National People's Congress (NPC), said
today that law-enforcement inspections of the Agriculture Law over
the past five years have increased Chinese farmers' awareness of
the need to protect their rights and interests in agriculture.
</P>
<P>
The inspections have provided a basis for changing the
fundamental status of agriculture as part of the nation's economy
and preserving the sanctity of law, he added.
</P>
<P>
The NPC Standing Committee's Agriculture Law inspection teams
for the Inner Mongolia Autonomous Region, and Yunnan, Jiangsu and
Guangdong provinces held a second meeting today in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Buhe told them that the law-enforcement inspection is helpful
for improving the Agriculture Law in accordance with the changing
situation and said that it must reflect problems discovered during
the inspection.
</P>
<P>
Inspectors should express their opinions and suggestions about
applying the Agriculture Law, agriculture investment, land
contracts, and establishing an agricultural protection mechanism
in accordance with the market economy, he noted. 
</P>
</TEXT>
