<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the
Kuala Lumpur Stock Exchange (KLSE) closed higher Thursday in
range-bound trading as institutional players maintained mild
support on key index-linked blue chips.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stocks Composite Index was up
11.20 points to 387.46, the all-share Emas Index added 2.66 points
to 102.37, the Industrial Index rose 23.69 points to 764.26 while
the Second Board Index was 0.69 of a point better at 94.40.
</P>
<P>
Gainers overwhelmed losers by 494 to 97 while 121 counters were
unchanged, 206 untraded and 39 counters suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's total turnover was lower at 167.726 million shares
valued at 274.321 million ringgit (72.189 million U.S. dollars)
from Wednesday's 198.689 million shares worth 296.105 million
ringgit (77.922 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The main board turnover was lower at 159.597 million shares
valued at 258.03 million ringgit (67.902 million U.S. dollars)
from 192.476 million shares amounting to 296.105 million ringgit
(75.39 million U.S. dollars) Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover was firmer with 8.129 million shares
worth 16.291 million ringgit (4.287 million U.S. dollars) from
6.213 million shares worth 9.621 million ringgit (2.531 million
U.S. dollars) Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Off-market turnover declined to 2.428 million shares valued at
5.043 million ringgit (1.327 million U.S. dollars) from 3.595
million shares worth 9.486 million ringgit (2.496 million U.S.
dollars) Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 7.230
million shares traded on the main board, industrial products
15.830 million shares, construction 18.014 million shares,
trading/services 48.229 million shares, infrastructure 716,000
shares, finance 23.279 million shares, hotels 680,000 shares,
properties 23.078 million shares, plantation 7.927 million shares,
mining 426,000 shares, trusts 96,000 shares, closed/fund 99,000
shares and loans 13.993 million shares. 
</P>
</TEXT>
