<HEADLINE> Landslide Kills Four in Bali, Indonesia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, September 24 (Xinhua) -- A landslide that followed
several days of heavy rains buried two houses in Duda village in
Indonesia's Bali province early Thursday, killing four people and
wounding two others.
</P>
<P>
The landslide also damaged five houses, a car, a motorcycle and
scores of electronic goods, Antara News Agency quoted spokesman of
the provincial police Maj. Y. Suyatmo as saying.
</P>
<P>
The heavy rains also caused another landslide in Alas Tungga
village in the province, but no casualty was reported, Suyatmo
added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
