<HEADLINE> Kyrgyz Receives ADB Infrastructure Loan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The Asian Development Bank
(ADB) announced Thursday that it has approved a
5-million-U.S.-dollar loan to the Kyrgyz Republic for
rehabilitation of flood-damaged infrastructure.
</P>
<P>
The Manila-based bank said the loan will be used to
rehabilitate roads and other infrastructure damaged by floods from
May to June this year in Jalal-Abad and Osh regions in the Central
Asian country.
</P>
<P>
The project will assist the government in easing hardship of
85,000 people, a large portion of whom live below the poverty
line.
</P>
<P>
The loan will come from the bank's Special Funds resources,
which means it is interest-free and repayable over 40 years,
including a grace period of 10 years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
