<HEADLINE> International Trendy Consumer Goods Fair in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NINGBO, September 24 (Xinhua) -- More than 100 overseas
businesspeople from 20 countries and regions will show their
latest consumer goods at an international fair scheduled for
mid-October here.
</P>
<P>
The forthcoming '98 Ningbo International Trendy Consumer Goods
Fair will be held in the bonded zone of Ningbo. The fair, which
is part of an international garment festival also in Ningbo
city, will feature new trends, styles and concepts, said
an organizer of the fair.
</P>
<P>
The fair will be held in eight halls with a combined floor
space of 10,000 sq m, and will have 200 business booths, said the
organizer.
</P>
<P>
Nine categories of commodities will be exhibited including
trendy automobiles, home appliances, handicrafts, garments,
footwear and headgear.
</P>
<P>
Multinational corporations such as Toyota, Sony, IBM,
Philip, and Siemens have agreed to display their lastest
products at the fair, according to him. 
</P>
</TEXT>
