<HEADLINE> Police in Southeastern China Arrest Drug Traffickers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Border police at Lianjiang in
China's Fujian Province have arrested 5 drug traffickers with
107.7 kilograms of "ice."
</P>
<P>
On the afternoon September 21, the Lianjiang border police,
working with local police, arrested Lin Qicheng, who was carrying
107.7 kilograms of "ice" in a taxi. Four other people were
arrested in the city of Lianjiang and in Guangdong Province, after
Lin was questioned.
</P>
<P>
All five have confessed to having been involved with the crime
and the case is still under investigation. 
</P>
