<HEADLINE> World Congress Of Architects In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The 20th World Congress of
the International Union of Architects (UIA) is scheduled to be
held in Beijing June 23, 1999, according to Wu Liangyong, vice
president of the Architecture Society of China.
</P>
<P>
Its theme is "Architecture in the 21st century", he says, with
6 sub-topics: "architecture and the environment", "architecture
and culture", "architecture and technology", "architecture and
professionalism", and "architectural education and young
architects".
</P>
<P>
Architects and officials from more than 100 countries and
regions are expected to attend the gathering, where there will be
reports on special topics and academic exchanges, and a series of
activities under the heading "urban housing for the 21st century",
with a student design competition, an exhibition, and a Chinese
architecture exhibition.
</P>
<P>
They will also publish a collection of papers and a
ten-volume work, "World Architecture: a Critical Mosaic,
1900-2000".
</P>
<P>
Architectural developments in the 21st century will be
discussed and conclusions on the development of architecture and
cities in the 20th century. 
</P>
