<HEADLINE> International Investment, Trade Fair in Northeastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HUNCHUN, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Agreements on 117 projects
involving 1.19 billion U.S. dollars worth of investment were
signed during the 1998 China Tumen River Valley Investment and
Trade Fair which ended Wednesday in the city of Hunchun in
northeast China's Jilin Province.
</P>
<P>
The projects include 56 in trade, and 24 in property. Business
people from more than 20 countries and regions attended the
three-day activity, which was sponsored by the United Nations
Industrial Development Organization (UNIDO), the UNDP, and the
Jilin Provincial Government.
</P>
<P>
In spite of the Asian financial crisis, businesses in many
countries are still interested in investment in the Tumen River
valley, according to UNIDO's chief representative in China.
</P>
<P>
UNIDO has pledged to support China, the Democratic People's
Republic of Korea, and Russia in developing the Tumen River
valley. The Tumen River flows along the Sino-DPRK border and
empties into the Sea of Japan on the Chinese-Russian border.
</P>
<P>
In the past six years, the Chinese goverment has spent 580
million U.S. dollars on infrastructure in the border economic
cooperation area at Hunchun, which has also got 120 million
U.S. dollars worth of overseas investment. 
</P>
