<HEADLINE> China's Innovative Internet Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- China has developed new
technology that it says will greatly improve quality and
reliability and cut cost of internet services that use
telecommunications networks.
</P>
<P>
Chinese told the Study Group 7 meeting of the International
Telecommunications Union's standardization department in Beijing
about using an optical cable network.
</P>
<P>
Herb Bertine, chairman of the Study Group 7, said that he is
surprised to see that China has been developing this technology
and equipment and that the technology is unique.
</P>
<P>
It combines the advantages of PPP and ATM technology that is
now widely used to connect the Internet with telecommunications
networks, with a performance to cost ratio many times higher than
that of existing technology.
</P>
<P>
The Wuhan Academy of Post and Telecommunications is developing
the technology and equipment. The academy's Yu Shaohu says that
since China has the largest optical cable network in the world,
the technology will greatly expand Internet use here.
</P>
<P>
China now has 120 million telephone lines. The figure is
expected to be 180 million by 2000. And, there are more than a
million Internet users in China.
</P>
<P>
Yu said that if the technology gets ITU approval, it will
create a new telecommunications technology and equipment
market. 
</P>
</TEXT>
