<HEADLINE> Symposium On Fish Utilization Opens In China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24,(Xinhua) -- A three-day symposium on
"Fish Utilization in the Asia-Pacific Region" opened in Beijing
today to discuss technology and consider recommendations for
future fishery research and development.
</P>
<P>
This is another meeting since the 1978 symposium in the
Philippines for the Asia Pacific Fishing Commission to discuss
this topic.
</P>
<P>
Fish have long been a traditional part of the diet in the Asia
Pacific Region and the fishing industry there has had developed
drapidly in the past years.
</P>
<P>
But since 1989, there have been declines in the fish supply,
and, what is worse, serious economic losses in catches and
processing. To protect the food supply and healthy fishing
development, the APFIC has decided that a symposium was a good
idea.
</P>
<P>
The APFIC is an affiliate of the Food and Agriculture
Organization. Some 100 People from 39 countries and regions are
participating in the Beijing session. 
</P>
