<HEADLINE> Sino-French Statement on Setting Up Cooperation Committee on Agriculture </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The governments of China and
France have decided to establish a committee on agriculture and
food under the Sino-French Mixed Committee for Economic and Trade
Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The new committee is aimed at promoting the realization of
Sino-French cooperation in agriculture as outlined in the
Sino-French Joint Statement signed by the two heads of state in
May 1997, according to a statement issued by the two governments
here today, following talks between Chinese Premier Zhu Rongji and
his French counterpart Lionel Jospin.
</P>
<P>
The committee, jointly headed by the agriculture ministers of
the two countries, will deal with issues concerning bilateral
cooperation in agriculture as referred to in the Sino-French Joint
Statement. The specific jobs are as follows:
</P>
<P>
-- Exchange and Cooperation on science, technology, and economy
and trade in the fields of agriculture and food processing,
especially exchanges in equipment and seeds, grape cultivation,
wine production, milk product, livestock, animal genes, irrigation
and grain;
</P>
<P>
-- The standards of agricultural product and food;
</P>
<P>
-- The protection of naming by the place of origin and the
crackdown on fake products;
</P>
<P>
-- Animal and plant quarantine; and
</P>
<P>
-- Coordination of the position of the two countries in major
international agricultural organizations.
</P>
<P>
The chairpersons of the committee will see to it that all
administrative departments concerned with these issues take part
in the committee.
</P>
<P>
The committee will hold annual sessions in each country in turn.
</P>
<P>
The committee pledges to share its information with the
Sino-French Mixed Committee for Economy and Trade. 
</P>
</TEXT>
