<HEADLINE> Share Prices Surge Up on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Share prices surged up on
Singapore Stock Market Thursday as Wall Street and regional stock
markets also climbed up.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) gained 30.99 points to
end at 931.98 points with a total turnover of 245.85 million units
worth 270.81 million Singapore dollars (157.68 million U.S.
dollars). Advancers outstripped decliners by 219 to 34 while 167
counters remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
ERL w01 was the most active stock of the day with a volume of
18.87 million stocks traded. It was followed by KepLand that had
17.05 million units done. DBS Land was next with 14.22 million
counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
CityDev topped the gainers of the day as it climbed 58 cents to
close at 3.60 Singapore dollars. Jurship went up 55 cents to
finish at 5.85 Singapore dollars. Creative 50 gained 40 cents to
end at 16.50 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Bukit Sem led the market's descent of the day
as it lost 20 cents to close at 6.30 Singapore dollars. H0 Roya
slid 13 cents to finish at 0.80 Singapore dollars. Seaview shed 10
cents to end at 3.30 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers said the markets were boosted by remarks of U.S.
Federal Reserve Chairman Alan Greenspan who said action must be
taken to tackle the contagion from the global financial crisis.
</P>
<P>
His remarks sent the Dow Jones Index surging as traders
believed the U.S. Federal Reserve might cut its interest rate and
such an action would be beneficial to investors. 
</P>
</TEXT>
