<HEADLINE> Chinese Foreign Ministry Comments On Human Rights </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Foreign Ministry Spokesman
Zhu Bangzao told a news conference here today that the fact that
the Chinese government will sign the International Covenant on
Civil and Political Rights in early October demonstrates China's
determination to promote and protect human rights.
</P>
<P>
He said that China respects the universality of human rights
and has taken legislative, judicial and administrative steps to
promote and protect the economic, cultural and civil rights of its
people.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese government has also placed great importance on
international conventions on human rights, and has contributed to
the promotion and maintenance of human rights, he said, and has
signed 17 international conventions on human rights, and is
willing to join the international community to improve human
rights worldwide.
</P>
<P>
Moreover, the Chinese government signed the International
Covenant on Economic, Social and Cultural Rights in October last
year. 
</P>
