<HEADLINE> Updates: Bomb Explodes at Jerusalem bus Stop </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, September 24 (Xinhua) -- A bomb exploded at a
Jerusalem bus stop during rush hours Thursday morning, injuring
an Israeli soldier and wrecking the stop's shelter.
</P>
<P>
Israeli police said the explosive device, weighing about one
kilogram and possibly triggered by a timer, went off at about
8:00 am (local time) near the campus of the Hebrew University,
East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
Shortly after the explosion, Israeli police and bomb squad
rushed to the scene and sealed the area, which is adjacent
to the West Bank. Police investigation team conducted searches
while the bomb squad combed the scene for other possible bombs.
</P>
<P>
An Israeli soldier sitting at the bus stop was lightly
hurt in the head when the bomb went off, the police said.
</P>
<P>
A white car with Palestinian license plates was seen leaving
the scene and was stopped at a nearby Israeli army roadblock and
the car driver was detained for questioning, the police added.
</P>
<P>
The police also used helicopters to search for suspects,
particularly the cars with Palestinian license plates.
</P>
<P>
The explosion occurred during the high alert period imposed by
the Israeli security forces two weeks ago following bomb treats
by Palestinian Islamic Resistance Movement (hamas) against the
Israelis. Hamas wants to avenge the killing of two Hamas members
earlier this month near Hebron by Israeli troops.
</P>
<P>
Thursday's bomb was relatively small and the bus stop was
located in an outlying neighborhood of Jerusalem. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
