<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Farmers in Mao Zedong's Native Place Become Well-off (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Farmers in the city of
Xiangtan in Hunan Province, near Mao Zedong's home are the first
group of people in Hunan to give shape to Mao's well-known line
"making the sun and the moon take on a new look", even though the
province is still underdeveloped as a whole.
</P>
<P>
According to a provincial rural development department, in the
past two decades, Xiangtan has led the province in developing its
rural economy.
</P>
<P>
One of these farmers is Tang Qilin. Sitting in a well-furnished
home, with a color TV, a washing-machine and a motorcycle, Tang
can hardly believe his eyes when he sees these things that have
come in the past six years.
</P>
<P>
"I could hardly make ends meet just a few years ago," says
Tang, but "thanks to the government's market-oriented economic
reform, we're now allowed to make money from whatever is
marketable." So he set up a pig farm in 1992 and now earns 200,000
a year.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, rural parts of Xiangtan produced over 35.8 billion
yuan in industrial and agricultural output, compared with 1.1
billion yuan in 1984. Per-capita income of local farmers was seven
times the 1984 figure at 2,532 yuan, 442 yuan more than the
national figure.
</P>
<P>
Township industries have grown in Xiangtan and produce 30
billion yuan worth of goods annually, compared with 372 million
yuan in 1984.
</P>
<P>
A recent survey made by the department shows that more than 85
percent of Xiangtan's rural residents are enjoying a relatively
comfortable life in terms of income, material and cultural life,
life expectancy, environment and social security.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
