<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Senior Chinese Official Arrives in New Zealand </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AUCKLAND, New Zealand, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Wei Jianxing,
member of the Political Bureau Standing Committee of the Central
Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC), arrived here on
an official goodwill visit to New Zealand after a successful visit
to Viet Nam.
</P>
<P>
In a written speech at the airport upon his arrival at the
biggest city of the country Wei said he was delighted to come to
visit "the homeland of Rewi Alley, a great son of New Zealand and
a friend of the Chinese people".
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese and New Zealand peoples enjoy a long-standing and
traditional friendship. The friendly relations of the two
countries have developed smoothly especially since the
establishment of the diplomatic ties. The two countries have
consistently deepened their exchange and cooperation in the
political, economic, trade, science and technology and cultural
fields," he said.
</P>
<P>
Wei, who is also a member of the Secretariat of the CPC Central
 Committee, noted that maintaining and promoting Sino-New Zealand
friendship is in the interest of the two peoples and conducive to
peace, stability and economic development in the Asian-Pacific
region and in the world at large.
</P>
<P>
He said he believed that his visit would push forward the
mutual understanding and friendship between the Chinese and New
Zealand peoples and the development of Sino-New Zealand
relations.
</P>
<P>
Wei's entourage includes Dai Bingguo, head of the International
 Liaison Department of the CPC Central Committee, and Yuan
Chunqing, member of the Standing Committee of the Central
Commission for Discipline Inspection of the CPC.
</P>
<P>
At the airport, Wei and his entourage were greeted by Chen
Wenzhao, Chinese ambassador to New Zealand, Wu Zuqiu, Chinese
consul-general in Auckland, and New Zealand government officials.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in New Zealand, Wei is scheduled to visit
Auckland, Rotorua and Wellington. 
</P>
</TEXT>
