friendship is in the interest of the two peoples and conducive to
peace, stability and economic development in the Asian-Pacific
region and in the world at large.
</P>
<P>
He said he believed that his visit would push forward the
mutual understanding and friendship between the Chinese and New
Zealand peoples and the development of Sino-New Zealand
relations.
</P>
<P>
Wei's entourage includes Dai Bingguo, head of the International
 Liaison Department of the CPC Central Committee, and Yuan
Chunqing, member of the Standing Committee of the Central
Commission for Discipline Inspection of the CPC.
</P>
<P>
At the airport, Wei and his entourage were greeted by Chen
Wenzhao, Chinese ambassador to New Zealand, Wu Zuqiu, Chinese
consul-general in Auckland, and New Zealand government officials.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in New Zealand, Wei is scheduled to visit
Auckland, Rotorua and Wellington. 
</P>
</TEXT>
