<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Restoration of UNITA Members' Positions in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUANDA, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The Angolan government has
reinstated a splinter group of the opposition UNITA movement in
the national reconciliation and unity government as from
Thursday.
</P>
<P>
A government statement issued Wednesday night said that the
decision was made in consideration of the fact "that the new
leadership of the National Union for Total Independence of Angola
(UNITA) has expressed their political attitude for the continued
peace process in the country."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Angolan President Eduardo dos Santos has removed
UNITA members, Marco Samondo as Minister of Geology and Mineral,
and Aurelio Joao Evangelista, as Deputy Minister of Social
Communication, for their continued loyalty to UNITA leader, Jonas
Savimbi.
</P>
<P>
On September 1, the government suspended UNITA members'
positions in the reconciliation and unity government for UNITA's
delay in implementing the 1994 Lusaka Peace Protocol group of
part of its armed forces, refusing to hand over four cities to
government administration and reluctance to move its headquarters
to Luanda.
</P>
<P>
A group of UNITA members in the government vowed to depose
Savimbi and set up a UNITA Renovation Committee, saying they
will stick to the peace process as stipulated by the 1994
Lusaka Peace Protocol.
</P>
<P>
Then Luanda cut off its ties with UNITA and recognizes the
UNITA Renovation Committee as the only partner to talk with in
the future.
</P>
<P>
But a recent resolution passed by the Security Council of the
United Nations has urged the Angolan government to continue its
peace talks with UNITA and U.N. Secretary General Kofi Annan also
demanded the government resume UNITA members' positions in the
reconciliation government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
