<HEADLINE> Uganda Suspends Operations of Bank </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Uganda's Trans-Africa Bank
Limited began to temporarily suspend operations Wednesday, a
third bank suspended in one week.
</P>
<P>
The suspension was made at the request of management,
Thursday's New Vision paper quoted Walugembe Musoke, the Bank of
Uganda (BOU) spokesman, as saying Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
He said the bank is not closed, but only suspends its
operations with the concurrence of BOU. The operations will
resume after the exercise of options is considered by the
share-holders.
</P>
<P>
A press release from the BOU said an inventory of all assets
and liabilities will be conducted by the central bank. It urged
customers to be patient during this period.
</P>
<P>
Earlier, International Credit Bank and Trust Bank were closed
for failing to rescue the falling Shilling. 
</P>
