<HEADLINE> Bangladesh Elected IAEA Vice-President </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, September 14 (Xinhua) -- Bangladesh has been elected
vice-president of the 42nd session of the general conference of
the International Atomic Energy Agency (IAEA), The New Nation
newspaper reported Thursday.
</P>
<P>
The conference, being held in Vienna and represented by 128
member states, is the most important annual event of this
specialized agency of the U.N. system.
</P>
<P>
Election of Bangladesh as a vice-president is seen as a
recognition of the country's impeccable credentials with regard to
peaceful application of atomic energy as well as its deep
commitment to non-proliferation of nuclear weapons, the report
pointed out.
</P>
<P>
The Bangladesh delegation is led by nuclear scientist M.A.
Wazed Miah, chairman of the Bangladesh Atomic Energy Commission,
and it will hold discussions on important bilateral matters with
the director general and other high officials of the IAEA as well
as delegations from different countries, the newspaper added.
</P>
</TEXT>
