<HEADLINE> AFC Draws Soccer Qualifiers for 2000 Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Thirty-four Asian teams will
compete for three soocer berths for the 2000 Olympic Games,
according to the Asian Football Confederation (AFC) which has
made the draws for the Asian Zone qualifiers.
</P>
<P>
The 34 teams will be divided into nine preliminary groups,
with the winners advancing to the second round. The nine winners
will later compete in the second round in three groups to vie for
the sole ticket allocated to each group for the Olympics.
</P>
<P>
Zhang Jilong, vice president of the Chinese Football
Association, said on Thursday that China is pitted in the Group G
against Vietnam, Myanmar and DPR Korea.
</P>
<P>
The preliminaries will run from February 1 to June 30 with the
final stage slated for September 1 to November 30 in 1999.
</P>
<P>
All the competitions will be run under the home-and-away
basis, Zhang added.
</P>
