<HEADLINE> Stability in Europe Depends on Russian Stability </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
VIENNA, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Russian Communist Party
Chairman Gennady Zyuganov said here Wednesday that stability in
Europe also depends on Russia's stability.
</P>
<P>
He said his country has sought ways to resolve its political
crisis, but the financial and social situation is still very
serious.
</P>
<P>
Some persons are critical of the military autocracy in Russia.
Zyuganov said the military dictatorship would not only cause the
disintegration of Russia, but could also bring disaster upon
Europe.
</P>
<P>
Russia needs new policies which will be in keeping with the
aspirations of people and the country's interest.
</P>
<P>
It is of significance that Russia expand economic and trade
relations with Western countries, especially now that winter is
coming. The party chairman said the winter season would be a
hungry winter for most parts of Russia. He asked Austria to
provide some economic help.
</P>
<P>
Zyuganov arrived here Wednesday for a brief visit. He met with
the president of the Austrian National Council, Heinz Fischer, and
Defense Minister Werner Fasslabend Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
He will return to Moscow Thursday morning. 
