<HEADLINE> Tianjin Development Zone Attracting Overseas Investors (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The Tianjin Economic and
Technological Development Zone, four kilometers from the port of
Tianjin, has become a popular investment site and an economic
powerhouse in this north China port city.
</P>
<P>
The zone, founded 14 years ago on a stretch of salt marshes, is
now home to 3,026 overseas-financed businesses involving a total
investment of over 10 billion U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Some 1,800 overseas-backed companies are now operational, said
Pi Qiansheng, head of the management committee for the Tianjin
Economic and Technological Zone.
</P>
<P>
A number of multinational corporations including Motorola, Coca
Cola, Samsung, and Novo Nordisk have been expanding their
operations in the zone.
</P>
<P>
Motorola of the United States, which has already pumped 1.1
billion U.S. dollars into the zone, will expand production
there by increasing its investment to 2.5 billion U.S. dollars
over the next few years.
</P>
<P>
Pi attributed the growing appeal of the development zone to an
improved investment environment, adherence to standard
international practices, and full use of the privileges bestowed
for piloting the socialist market economy.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
