<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tianjin Development Zone Attracting Overseas Investors (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
With a planned area of 33 square kilometers, the Tianjin
Economic and Technological Development Zone is the largest
development zone in the country.
</P>
<P>
The zone has so far invested 7 billion yuan for infrastructure
construction on 40 square kilometers of reclaimed land, 22 of
which are inside the development zone and the remainder in the
Hangu and Xiqing districts and Wuqing County. Also, 30 billion
yuan has been invested in fixed assets on the reclaimed land where
buildings with a combined floor space of three million square
meters have been completed.
</P>
<P>
Supported by the four major industries of electronics,
bio-pharmaceuticals, precision machinery, and foodstuffs, the
Tianjin Economic and Technological Development Zone consists of
many industrial parks, and it has been expanding at an average
annual economic growth rate of 60 percent, according to Pi.
</P>
<P>
Information from the Special Economic Zones Office of the State
Council also shows that the Tianjin Zone has led the country's 32
state-level development zones in 14 major economic indicators
since the beginning of the year.
</P>
<P>
In the first half of this year, the zone produced 8.84 billion
yuan in gross domestic product (GDP), produced 24.85 billion yuan
worth of industrial goods, exported commodities valued at 1.04
billion U.S. dollars and generated 1.33 billion yuan in tax
revenue, Pi said.
</P>
<P>
Pi added that by the year 2000, the development zone, 45 kilometers
from the city of Tianjin proper, will have a contractual inflow of
11 billion U.S. dollars in overseas investment, and 25 billion yuan
in domestic investment. By then, it will be able to produce 117
billion yuan worth of manufactured goods and generate 43 billion
yuan of GDP.  
</P>
</TEXT>
