<HEADLINE> Shanghai On-Line Attracts More Visitors </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai On-Line has become
one of the most popular websites in China after two years of
expansion.
</P>
<P>
To date, Shanghai On-Line, the largest local public information
network in this metropolis, has received some 11.5 million visits,
with the number of daily visits soaring to 30,000 to 40,000 from
only several hundred two years ago, according to the Shanghai
Information Industry Co. Ltd.
</P>
<P>
The website, already linked with several local and national
multimedia networks, provides information in 24 different
categories and visitors can now hold talks and conduct other
interactive activities.
</P>
<P>
On-line business services, opened two years ago, including
shopping are now very active on the site, and people have begun to
use the network for real estate and stock trading.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai On-Line is now capable of receiving 4,300 visits at
any one time following the completion of the second-phase
expansion. More than 180,000 users have become frequent visitors,
among which over 50,000 are registered subscribers.
</P>
<P>
The third-phase of expansion is now underway and is expected to
increase the number of registered subscribers to 150,000 and allow
one-million people to browse it daily.  
</P>
</TEXT>
