<HEADLINE> China Ranks First in Artificial Diamond Production </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ZHENGZHOU, September 24 (Xinhua) -- China led the world in the
production of artificial diamonds in 1997 with a total output of
100,000 kg of the hardest material in existence.
</P>
<P>
Artificial diamonds have been widely used in China's
machine-building, petroleum, geological prospecting and automobile
manufacturing industries, according information released during a
recent international seminar on super-hard materials and related
finished products. The seminar was held in Zhengzhou, capital of
central China's Henan Province,
</P>
<P>
China is working diligently to improve the quality of
artificial diamonds, according to experts attending the event.
