<HEADLINE> Brazil's Oil Production Grows in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's oil
production rose by 1.74 percent in August, the country's state oil
company Petrobres said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The company said national oil production in August amounted to
1.6 million barrels per day (bpd), an increase of 20,000 barrels
over July's production.
</P>
<P>
The state of Rio de Janeiro, where the country's major oil
field -- the Bay of Fields -- is located, generated 73.03 percent
of the country's total production.
</P>
<P>
Brazil, whose domestic crude oil consumption is close to 1.8
million bpd, has to import 800,000 bpd of crude oil, the company
said. 
</P>
