<HEADLINE> Modern International Port For Northeastern China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENYANG, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Thanks to its geographical
conditions, the city of Dandong in China's Liaoning Province has
been building itself into a modern international port.
</P>
<P>
Dandong has six kilometers of coastline and two ports, Langtou
and Dadong, with a total handling capacity of 2.15 million tons
and shipping to over 30 countries and regions.
</P>
<P>
Analysts say that more than 30 berths with more than 20 million
tons handling capacity could be built at Dadong. Handling capacity
is expected to rise to 5.5 million tons by the year 2000 and to 12
million tons in 2010. The provincial government plans to increase
annual handling capacity of Dandong harbor to 15 million tons in
2020.
</P>
<P>
The city of Dandong has a comprehensive transport network of
railways, highways, ships, and aircraft that has been playing an
important role in economic development in northeastern China.
</P>
</TEXT>
