<HEADLINE> Italian Wins Stage in Tour of Spain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Fabrizio Guidi of Italy won
his third victory by finishing first in the sprint dash in the
18th stage of the Tour of Spain on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Guidi covered the 223 kilometers from Leon to Salamanca in 5
hours 59 minutes and 40 seconds, his third win in the 22-stage
Spanish tour.
</P>
<P>
However, Spaniard Abraham Olano remained the overall leader.
</P>
<P>
The leaders were virtually unchanged as several breakaway
attempts were neutralized and the cyclists rode in a relatively
relaxed pace until the final sprint.
</P>
<P>
With four stages to go, Olano remained 22 seconds clear of
Frenchman Laurent Jalabert of the ONCE-Deutsche Bank team. Olano
also stayed 31 seconds ahead of his Banesto teammate and fellow
Spaniard Jose Maria Jimenez.
</P>
<P>
Thursday's 19th stage will test the climbing abilities with a
170.4-kilometer run between the towns of Avila and Segovia in the
mountains north of Madrid. 
</P>
