<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Chinese International Scores in England </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese international Fan
Zhiyi, who joined the English club Crystal Palace this summer,
scored his first goal in three matches, helping the club beat
Bury 2-1 Wednesday evening.
</P>
<P>
Teenager Clinton Morrison went from hero to zero with a goal
at either end as Palace failed to elbow a way into the third
round of the English League Worthington Cup.
</P>
<P>
Crystal Palace lost the second round first leg 3-0 to Bury,
which advanced with an aggregate score of 4-2.
</P>
<P>
Morrison, a 19-year-old local boy making his first start for
the club and only his seventh appearance, gave them a dream
opening in the eighth minute.
</P>
<P>
Hayden Mullins threaded the ball out to the right of the Bury
area from where the youngster cut in to finish superbly with a
shot across and into the goal.
</P>
<P>
Morrison's joy lasted only 17 minutes. Palace's Rob Matthews
sent over a long swerving corner which the defending striker
sliced into his own net.
</P>
<P>
At the 77th minute, Chinese midfielder Fan Zhiyi shot from 10
yards, which made the score at 2-1.
</P>
<P>
Another Chinese player Sun Jihai, who also plays for Crystal
Palace, was sidelined due to ankle injury.
</P>
<P>
Premier league Southampton's unhappy start to the season
gathered pace on the day when they were dumped out of the English
League Cup by second division Fulham.
</P>
<P>
Southampton, bottom of the league, had former England defender
Carlton Palmer sent off as they stumbled to a 1-0 defeat in the
home leg of their second round tie.
</P>
<P>
Dirk Lehmann earned Fulham a 2-1 aggregate win with a strike
after just 10 minutes. Palmer was shown the red card after
clashing with Lehmann in the 36th minute.
</P>
<P>
The three other premier league sides in action made it through
to the third round but Tottenham and Everton did not have things
all their own way.
</P>
<P>
Tottenham started badly against third division Brentford,
falling behind to an Andy Scott goal after just 52 seconds to
make the aggregate score 3-3.
</P>
<P>
Allan Nielsen settled the premier league side's nerves with a
24th minute equaliser, central defender Sol Campbell put them 2-1
ahead on the night with a diving header in the 46th minute and
Chris Armstrong added a third after seven minutes later.
</P>
<P>
Lloyd Owusu scored a second for Brentford in the 74th minute
but Spurs held on to win 3-2.
</P>
<P>
Everton, reduced to 10 men in the 70th minute of their home
leg against Huddersfield, fell behind after just 44 seconds
against the first division leaders. Marcus Stewart put
Huddersfield 2-1 ahead on aggregate.
</P>
<P>
Everton equalised through Frenchman Olivier Dacourt's 25-meter
free kick in the 29th minute and Marco Materazzi put them 3-2
ahead on aggregate three minutes before halftime.
</P>
<P>
But they faced a difficult final 20 minutes after Materazzi
was dismissed for an off-the-ball incident.
</P>
<P>
A 27th minute Paulo Wanchope goal gave premier league Derby a
1-0 away win over second division Manchester City and a 2-1
aggregate triumph.
</P>
<P>
Holders Chelsea enter the competition in the next round.
</P>
</TEXT>
