<HEADLINE> Badaling Expressway Set for Completion </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The two hour journey from
downtown Beijing to the Badaling Section of the Great Wall will be
shortened to only 40 minutes when second phase construction of the
final two sections open to traffic at the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
The six-lane expressway will not only be one of longest of the
capital city's five major expressways, but is also expected to
become one of the busiest arteries leading to famous tourist
sites. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
