<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Expressway For East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Work on a new expressway
started recently in Zhejiang, a coastal province in east China.
</P>
<P>
The 118-km highway connects Jinhua, a major city in central
Zhejiang, with Wenzhou, an economic center in the southeastern
part of the province.
</P>
<P>
It is part of the provincial highway network, and is expected
to help economic development in Lishui, Jinhua and Wenzhou.
</P>
<P>
Its cost is estimated at 4.6 billion yuan. It will be completed
in 2002. 
</P>
</TEXT>
