<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Brazil Ties Yugoslavia 1-1 in Exhibition Soccer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, September 23 (Xinhua) -- In its first match
under coach Wanderley Luxemburgo, Brazil tied Yugoslavia 1-1 in
Sao Luis on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslavia scored the opener when Milosevic chipped in a shot
from a long pass in the 7th minute.
</P>
<P>
Brazil that fielded in three World Cup veterasn, netted in the
equaliser in the 16th minute as Marcelinho curled his free kick
into the right corner.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslavia lost a man in the 50th minute when Grozdic was
given a red card after tackling Marcelinho from behind, but
Brazil was unable to capitalize on the one man advantage.
</P>
<P>
"I think as a first test it was a good game," said Luxemburgo
after the match, "Their team is very strong and very experienced.
Even with a man down they managed to secure the game."
</P>
<P>
Lineups:
</P>
<P>
Brazil: Andre, Cafu, Antonio Carlos, Cleber, Serginho Felipe,
Marcos Assuncao, Rogerio Vampeta, Jackson Marcelinho, Christian
Rivaldo, Muller and Alex Denilson.
</P>
<P>
Yugoslavia: Zilic Krajl, Nadj Ngegus, Savic, Djukic, Djorovic,
Sarac Stanovic, Jokanovic, Grozdic, Curcic Petrovic, Kovacevic
Milosevic, Mijatovic. 
</P>
</TEXT>
