<HEADLINE> Sea-spanning Bridge Under Construction in Haikou </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, September 24 (Xinhua) -- Haikou, capital of south
China's island province of Hainan, is building a sea-spanning
bridge which will link the city with several surrounding islands.
</P>
<P>
The 2,663-meter-long bridge is designed to connect downtown
Haikou with two islands, a development zone and a new
city area.
</P>
<P>
The project costs 667 million yuan (about 80 million
U.S. dollars) including 50 million U.S. dollars in
bank loans from Japan.
</P>
<P>
The bridge, named the Century Bridge, will be another
Haikou landmark when completed in 2001. 
</P>
</TEXT>
