<HEADLINE> Lhasa Introduce More Combines for Autumn Harvest </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The Farm and Animal Husbandry
Bureau in Lhasa, capital of the Tibet Autonomous Region, has just
purchased 26 combines to prepare for autumn harvest.
</P>
<P>
The combines represent the initial mechanization of the city's
agricultural sector and greatly facilitate the autumn harvest,
according to bureau officials.
</P>
<P>
The autumn harvest is the most important for local farmers in
Tibet, with the plateau region featuring harsh climatic conditions
quite different from other parts of the country.
</P>
<P>
Thirty local farmers have been trained to operate the new
machinery and six experts from the manufacturing company have have
been invited to give lectures.  
</P>
</TEXT>
