<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spain Beats Russia in Soccer Friendly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Spain defeated Russia 1-0 in
a soccer friendly in Granada on Wednesday, awarding Jose Antonio
Camacho his first victory in his first outing as coach of the
national squad.
</P>
<P>
Bittor Alkiza scored the lone goal in the 39th minute with a
curving left foot shot from outside the box.
</P>
<P>
Camacho had included seven changes in the squad with three new
faces, including Alkiza in an aim to wipe out the sad memories as
Spain was recently defeated by Cyprus 3-2 and kicked out of the
first round in the World Cup finals.
</P>
<P>
Against a capacity stadium, the Russians failed to take full
advantage when defender Sergi Barjuan was sent off in the 26th
minute for a bungled block in front of the Spanish goal.
</P>
<P>
A diving save from Santiago Canizares prevented Alexander
Mostovoi from converting the penalty.
</P>
<P>
Down to 10 men, Spain sealed the final scoreline when Alkiza
scored six minutes before the break.
</P>
<P>
Camacho took over from Javier Clemente after six years on the
job. Spain failed to win a single title during Clemente's reign.
</P>
</TEXT>
