<HEADLINE> Chinese FM Meets With UN Secretary-General </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 23 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign
Minister Tang Jiaxuan on Wednesday met with U.N. Secretary-General
Kofi Annan.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Tang, who is here to attend the 53rd
session of the General Assembly, said as a most universal
international organization, the United Nations was playing a more
and more important role in world's affairs, a role that could not
be substituted.
</P>
<P>
Tang highly praised the U.N. Secretary-General by saying
that he had played a key role in resolving regional crises
and conflicts.
</P>
<P>
Tang said China would, as always, attach great importance to
developing its relations with the United Nations and would
continue to support the United Nations in its mandate entrusted in the
United Nations Charter.
</P>
<P>
For his part, Annan said China had played a stabilizing role
in Asia's financial crisis, and China and U.N. had enjoyed good
cooperation in regional and international affairs.
</P>
<P>
The Secretary-General said the United Nations high
Commissioner for Human Rights, Mary Robinson, had just concluded
her visit to China, and the visit was a very successful one.  
</P>
</TEXT>
