<HEADLINE> Albright Says More Work Needed on Middle East Peace Talks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 23 (Xinhua) -- U.S. Secretary of
State Madeleine Albright said on Wednesday that there was still a
lot of work to do to reach an agreement between Israel and the
Palestinians.
</P>
<P>
"We are taking it one step at a time. I am an eternal
optimist. We have made some progress. We have a lot of work to
do," Albright said after a talk with Israeli Prime Minister
Benjamin Netanyahu.
</P>
<P>
Israel and the Palestinians are at odds over a U.S.
initiative under which Israel would hand over an additional 13
percent of the West Bank in exchange for Palestinian security
measures of fighting terrorism.  
