<DOCNO> XIE19980924.0323 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-09-24 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hostage Crisis Ends Violently in Athens </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, September 24 (Xinhua) -- The hostage crisis in the
Greek capital of Athens ended later Wednesday night with eight
people being injured, including three in critical condition.
</P>
<P>
When police launched an assault on the Romanian criminal at
large who held four hostages as of early Wednesday evening, the
Romanian man booby-trapped a handgrenade inside the woman
hostage's underwear and unleashed the pin just before pushing her
at oncoming police commandos.
</P>
<P>
The escaped Romanian convict, a woman hostage and a police
officer were seriously injured in the blast while five other
police officers were slightly injured.
</P>
<P>
The 27-year Soren Matei, who earlier this month in Athens took
a policeman hostage for eight hours after fleeing from police, was
reported on Wednesday as holding two men and two women at an
apartment off Acharnon street in central Athens.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian man had demanded 500,000 U.S. dollars for his
escape and for the release of the hostages.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
